President Obama announced his intent to nominate Kristine L. Svinicki for the position of Commissioner of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC). Svinicki has been a Commissioner of the NRC since 2008 and has a background in nuclear engineering. She has previously worked as a professional staff member on the Senate Armed Services Committee and as a senior policy advisor to Senators John Warner and John McCain. Svinicki also has experience working in the U.S. Department of Energy. She holds a B.S. in Nuclear Engineering from the University of Michigan.